        "title": "[Feature]: Channel Broker Phase 2C Discord migration proof",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Adds the Phase 2C Discord broker routing proof on top of #86137, #86133, and #86096.\n- Normalizes broker-routed Discord DMs and channel threads without importing native Discord extension internals.\n- Preserves non-channel conversation type in canonical broker routes so Discord DMs remain direct routes.\n\n## Rollout Context\n\nCloses #86111\nRelated #86108\nRelated #86105\nStacked on #86137\nStacked on #86133\nStacked on #86096\n\nNative Discord defaults stay unchanged. Existing prefix ownership still keeps `discord:` owned by the native Discord plugin when installed; this PR proves the opt-in broker route through `broker:discord:...` and the broker alias path when native Discord is absent.\n\nFor review, the focused stack diff is:\nhttps://github.com/100yenadmin/openclaw/compare/feat/channel-broker-telegram-routing...feat/channel-broker-discord-routing\n\n## Real Behavior Proof\n\n### Behavior\n\nOpenClaw can represent Discord DMs and channel threads through `channel-broker` using stable broker semantics: provider platform `discord`, direct/channel conversation type, conversation id, and optional thread id.\n\n### Environment\n\n- Local checkout: `/Volumes/LEXAR/repos/openclaw-channel-broker`\n- Branch: `feat/channel-broker-discord-routing`\n- Head: `e5c1b9c685 Add Discord broker routing proof`\n\n### Steps\n\n1. Sent a synthetic message to `broker:discord:user:123456789012345678`.\n2. Verified the provider request used `platform: \"discord\"`, `conversation.type: \"direct\"`, and `conversation.id: \"123456789012345678\"`.\n3. Sent a synthetic message to `broker:discord:channel:222222222222222222?threadId=333333333333333333`.\n4. Verified the provider request used channel conversation id plus `threadId`.\n5. Resolved the outbound session route for the Discord DM target.\n6. Verified the route stayed direct and canonicalized to `discord:direct%3A123456789012345678`.\n\n### Evidence\n\n- `pnpm exec vitest run extensions/channel-broker/src/channel.test.ts extensions/channel-broker/src/conformance.test.ts --config test/vitest/vitest.extension-channel-broker.config.ts`\n  - 2 files passed, 13 tests passed.\n- `pnpm exec tsc --noEmit -p extensions/channel-broker/tsconfig.json`\n  - passed.\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check extensions/channel-broker/src/target.ts extensions/channel-broker/src/channel.ts extensions/channel-broker/src/channel.test.ts`\n  - passed.\n- `pnpm exec oxlint extensions/channel-broker --format unix`\n  - passed.\n- `git diff --check`\n  - passed.\n\n### Observed Result\n\nDiscord DMs and threads now flow through broker target parsing and provider request semantics, not through core or native Discord extension branches.\n\n### Not Tested\n\n- Live Discord API traffic; this PR is the opt-in broker migration proof, not a live provider connector.\n- Full local suite. Per `/Volumes/LEXAR` policy, broad validation is left to GitHub Actions.\n\n## Current Upstream Gate Context\n\nPR #86096 currently has one unrelated `checks-node-agentic-agents` CI timeout in `src/agents/model-catalog-visibility.test.ts`; the failed test is outside this broker stack. I attempted to rerun the failed job, but GitHub blocked it because this account does not have repository admin rights.\n",
